Bangers and Mash with Guiness Onion Gravy
  --Cook's Country

2 lb Yukon gold potatoes, peeled and cut into 1" pieces
1/2 tsp table salt + salt for cooking potatoes
3/4 c half-and-half, warmed
10 tbsp unsalted butter, divided
2 lb bratwurst
1 onion, halved and sliced thin
1 1/2 tbsp ap flour
3/4 c beef broth
3/4 c Guinness Draught beer
1 tbsp Dijon mustard
1/2 tsp pepper

Combine potatoes and 1 tbsp salt in large saucepan and add water to cover by 1". Bring to boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until potatoes are fork-tender, 15-20 min. Drain potatoes and return to saucepan. Add half-and-half and 5 tbsp butter. Using potato masher, mash potatoes in saucepan until smooth. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Meanwhile, melt 1 tbsp butter in 12" nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add bratwursts and cook until well browned on 2 sides, ~5 min. Transfer bratwursts to plate. Wipe skillet clean with paper towels. Add 2 tbsp butter, onion, and salt to now-empty skillet and cook until onion is softened and lightly browned, 4-6 min. Stir in flour and cook for 1 min. Whisk in broth, Guinness, mustard, and pepper. Add bratwursts and bring to simmer. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover; and cook until bratwursts register 160F, 10-12 min. Transfer bratwursts to serving platter. Off heat, stir remaining 2 tbsp butter into onion mixture. Serve bratwurst with mashed potatoes and spoon onion mixture over top.




Notes: Do not use Guinness Extra Stout. Garnish with chopped fresh chives or other fresh herbs, if desired.
